If I’m honest, we’re still doing that, just from a different venue. One insight I can share about bands in the contemporary milieu is that they can be little more than glorified WhatsApp groups. This is awesome, because hirsute, jaunty young rakes are at their best when sharing tongue-in-cheek banter. Our band was a group of five in the traditional rock format and we would filter into the dealership in dribs and drabs every Friday evening to run through a selection of rough-and-ready originals. Picking our way past rows of Big Boy scooters, pit bikes and some masculine superbikes, we...